**We don't recommend using [importmap](https://github.com/rails/importmap-rails) with Fox Tail UI project.**

If you currently are using importmaps with your Rails project, you might want to consider migrating over to an asset bundler
before considering using this project.

## Install Tailwind CSS

1. Add the [cssbundling-rails](https://github.com/rails/cssbundling-rails) GEM

    ```shell
    bundle add cssbundling-rails
    ```

2. Run

    ```shell
    rails css:install:tailwind
    ```

## Install Flowbite

1. Add the Flowbite NPM package

    ```shell
    npm install flowbite
    ```

2. Include Flowbite as a plugin inside the `tailwind.config.js` file.

    ```javascript
    module.exports = {

        plugins: [
            require('flowbite/plugin')
        ]
    }
    ```

## Install JS Bundler

1. Add the [jsbundling-rails](https://github.com/rails/jsbundling-rails) GEM

    ```ruby
    bundle add 'jsbundling-rails'
    ```

2. Run

   ```shell
   rails javascript:install:[bun|esbuild|rollup|webpack]
   ```

## Install Stimulus

1. Add the [Stimulus](https://stimulus.hotwired.dev/) NPM package

    ```shell
    npm install @hotwired/stimulus
   ```

## Install Fox Tail

1. Add the GEM

    ```ruby
   bundle add fox_tail
    ```

2. Add the NPM package

    ```shell
    npm install @jfawks/fox_tail
    ```

3. Include Fox Tail as a plugin to inside the `tailwind.config.js` file

    ```javascript
   const path = require('node:path')
   const { execSync } = require('node:child_process');
   const foxTailPath = execSync('bundle show fox_tail').toString();

    module.exports = {
        darkMode: 'class',

        content: [
            path.join(foxTailPath, "app/components/fox_tail/**/*.{ts,theme.yml}")
        ],

        plugins: [
            require('flowbite/plugin'),
            require('@jfawks/fox_tail/plugin')
        ]
    }
    ```

4. Register the Stimulus controllers in your `application.js` file

    ```javascript
    import {Application} from "@hotwired/stimulus";
    import {registerControllers} from '@jfawks/fox_tail';

    window.Stimulus = Application.start();
    registerControllers(Stimulus);
   ```
